  "prompt": "Why don't people answer me on Quora?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why people might not be answering you on Quora. Here are some possible explanations:\n\n1. **Question Clarity**: If your question is unclear, too broad, or ambiguous, people might not understand what you're asking and therefore won't respond. Make sure your question is specific and well-written.\n\n2. **Topic Niche**: If your question is about a very niche or obscure topic, there might be fewer people who have the knowledge or interest to answer it. Consider broadening the scope or rephroring it to attract more responses.\n\n3. **Engagement**: If you\u2019re new to Quora or have low engagement (few followers, no profile picture, or limited activity), people might be less likely to notice or respond to your question. Building a presence on the platform can help.\n\n4. **Question Repetition**: If your question has been asked and answered many times before, people might skip it. Check the platform to see if a similar question already exists and consider reading those answers instead.\n\n5. **Timing**: Sometimes, it\u2019s a matter of timing. If you post a question when fewer people are active, it might not get noticed. Try posting at different times to increase visibility.\n\n6. **Tone or Approach**: If your question comes across as demanding, rude, or unprofessional, people might be less inclined to respond. A polite and respectful tone can encourage more engagement.\n\n7. **Lack of Expertise**: Some questions require specialized knowledge, and there might not be enough experts on Quora who can provide a satisfactory answer.\n\n8. **Algorithm Issues**: Quora's algorithm might not be surfacing your question to the right audience. Using relevant topics, tags, and keywords can help.\n\n9. **User Behavior**: Some users only answer questions from people they follow or questions that appear in their feed. If your question doesn\u2019t reach the right audience, it might go unnoticed.\n\n10. **Question Length**: If your question is too long or contains unnecessary details, people might lose interest before getting to the point. Keep it concise and to the point.\n\nTo improve your chances of getting answers:\n\n- Write clear, concise, and specific questions.\n- Use relevant topics and tags.\n- Engage with the community by answering questions or participating in discussions.\n- Be patient and consider rephrasing or reposting your question if it doesn\u2019t get a response initially.\n\nRemember, Quora is a community-driven platform, and building relationships and credibility can help you get more responses over time.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
